    <p>Re•mix 2k21: Fash­ion De­sign Com­pe­ti­tion</p>
    <p>The Sin­ga­pore Chi­nese Cul­tural Cen­tre in­vites stu­dents aged 15 to 25 with a keen in­ter­est in fash­ion de­sign to take part in the in­au­gu­ral Re•mix 2k21 Fash­ion De­sign Com­pe­ti­tion. Par­tic­i­pants should get their in­spi­ra­tion from the Sin­gapo(ren): Dis­cov­er­ing Chi­nese Sin­ga­porean Cul­ture per­ma­nent ex­hi­bi­tion at the cen­tre. Works of the fi­nal­ists will be ex­hib­ited dur­ing the Re•mix 2k21 fes­ti­val at the venue. Cash prizes are up for grabs.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Dead­line for ap­pli­ca­tion & sub­mis­sion of sketches is today INFO: sin­ga­poreccc.org.sg/event/ remix2k21­fash­ion</p>
    <p>SMHFF Short Film Youth Com­pe­ti­tion 2021</p>
    <p>The Sin­ga­pore Men­tal Health Film Fes­ti­val (SMHFF)</p>
    <p>Short Film Youth Com­pe­ti­tion is back for the sec­ond year. Those aged 15 to 35 are in­vited to pro­duce a short film that fea­tures one of the fol­low­ing top­ics: sui­cide preven­tion, re­cov­ery, cy­ber bul­ly­ing, life tran­si­tions and young care­givers. There will also be three film pro­duc­tion work­shops. The winning film will be screened at SMHFF 2021 in May next year at Na­tional Gallery Sin­ga­pore and also at the New York City Men­tal Health Film Fes­ti­val and Ren­dezvous with Mad­ness Fes­ti­val in Toronto, Canada. The top three films will win cash prizes of up to $3,000.</p>
    <p>WHEN: Reg­is­tra­tion closes on Nov 30 INFO: bit.ly/3jigccC</p>


